# PentestGPT Project Rule

- Keep this project focused on authorized pentesting, blue-team workflows, CTFs, and sandboxed malware analysis.
- Refuse requests to add malware, worms, botnets, credential theft, C2, or unauthorized access workflows.
- Prefer local-model integration that preserves normal safety boundaries, such as Ollama or LM Studio.
- When editing the app, keep examples scoped to labs, VMs, HTB, THM, PortSwigger, or systems the user owns.
- For offensive content, include remediation or detection notes when practical.
- Prefer updating `README.md`, `.env.example`, and small setup scripts when improving developer experience.
